{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>In this family there are leader peptides involved in the regulation of the glutaminase subunit (small subunit) of arginine-specific carbamoyl phosphate synthetase. In Neurospora crassa it is a small upstream ORF of 24 codons above the arg-2 locus [[cite:PUB00002557]]. In yeast it is the leader peptide of the CPA1 gene. The 5' region of CPA1 mRNA contains a 25 codon upstream open reading frame. The leader peptide, the product of the upstream open reading frame, plays an essential, negative role in the specific repression of CPA1 by arginine [[cite:PUB00017104]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF08252" "arg-2/CPA1 leader peptide"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Leader peptide, Arg-2/CPA1", "short" "Leader_Arg2_CPA1"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 1, "domain_architectures" 4, "proteomes" 41, "taxa" 256, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 73, "sets" 0, "proteins" 73, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 63}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR013203", :literature {"PUB00002557" {"URL" nil, "issue" "19", "authors" ["Orbach MJ" "Sachs MS" "Yanofsky C."], "ISO_journal" "J. Biol. Chem.", "DOI_URL" "http://intl.jbc.org/cgi/content/abstract/265/19/10981", "medline_journal" "J Biol Chem", "title" "The Neurospora crassa arg-2 locus. Structure and expression of the gene encoding the small subunit of arginine-specific carbamoyl phosphate synthetase.", "year" 1990, "raw_pages" "10981-7", "volume" "265", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 2141606}, "PUB00017104" {"URL" nil, "issue" "6", "authors" ["Werner M" "Feller A" "Messenguy F" "Pierard A."], "ISO_journal" "Cell", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0092-8674(87)90618-0", "medline_journal" "Cell", "title" "The leader peptide of yeast gene CPA1 is essential for t